00:18:54.000 --> 00:18:57.000
I appreciate that you brought this up in your talk.

00:18:57.000 --> 00:19:00.000
And I'm wondering if you can say more about your experience being a white man.

00:19:01.000 --> 00:19:05.000
Starting that journey of learning the language and reconciliation.

00:19:06.000 --> 00:19:07.000
Yeah.

00:19:08.000 --> 00:19:10.000
Yeah, so this was quite challenging.

00:19:10.000 --> 00:19:16.000
It's actually something that I've had multiple kind of little things that contributed to this.

00:19:16.000 --> 00:19:22.000
I've had lots of times when I've spoken to people who have given really good pieces of advice.

00:19:24.000 --> 00:19:25.000
Things like...

00:19:26.000 --> 00:19:27.000
So a really important point.

00:19:27.000 --> 00:19:33.000
One thing that I've been taught is that we have this tendency to say like the indigenous culture.

00:19:33.000 --> 00:19:36.000
But that's quite wrong.

00:19:36.000 --> 00:19:42.000
Back home, there are lots of different Maori groups who have their own traditions and opinions.

00:19:42.000 --> 00:19:45.000
And that can be challenging because it's hard to know.

00:19:46.000 --> 00:19:47.000
It's not like...

00:19:47.000 --> 00:19:48.000
There is not one right way.

00:19:48.000 --> 00:19:53.000
So some people might not necessarily agree with the idea of me using a pepiha.

00:19:53.000 --> 00:19:55.000
Some people might say that I should do a pepiha.

00:19:55.000 --> 00:20:01.000
But it would be quite different to if it was used by an indigenous person.

00:20:01.000 --> 00:20:02.000
It's been difficult.

00:20:02.000 --> 00:20:07.000
But by speaking to lots of people, it's helped to understand that there are different points.

00:20:07.000 --> 00:20:10.000
And then by, I think, just sort of trying to find the consensus.

00:20:10.000 --> 00:20:15.000
I've also received a really positive thought, which is that intention is very important.

00:20:15.000 --> 00:20:18.000
So by having the right intention, that goes a long way.

00:20:19.000 --> 00:20:24.000
Personally, that helped a lot because, you know, no one wants to make a mistake and to blunder or to offend anyone.

00:20:24.000 --> 00:20:27.000
But hearing that my intention was very important, that helped a lot.

